	&lt;section id=\&quot;tools\&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div class=\&quot;page-header\&quot;&gt;
		&lt;h2&gt;
			Create a sample audio&lt;/h2&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;
		You may need modify the audio of your projects several times during development. I therefore recommend use a TTS like &lt;a href=\&quot;http://www2.research.att.com/~ttsweb/tts/demo.php\&quot;&gt;AT&amp;amp;T Natural Voices&amp;reg; Text-to-Speech Demo&lt;/a&gt;. Of course to put in production is better use a real human voice.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/section&gt; &lt;section id=\&quot;convert\&quot;&gt;
	&lt;div class=\&quot;page-header\&quot;&gt;
		&lt;h2&gt;
			Convert from wav to gsm&lt;/h2&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;
		If you need to convert you a wav audio to gsm, &amp;nbsp;go to your audio directory and run the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;pre&gt;
for a in *.wav; do sox &amp;quot;$a&amp;quot; -r 8000 -c1 &amp;quot;`echo $a|sed -e s/wav//`gsm&amp;quot; resample -ql; done&amp;nbsp;
&lt;/pre&gt;
	&lt;/section&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
